# Testing Standards

Write tests that validate behavior users experience.

## Rules

- Prefer `@testing-library/react` queries by role/label/text over implementation details.
- Include at least one interaction test for interactive components.
- Assert behavior and accessibility state, not Tailwind class names.
- Mock framework-specific components only when necessary (for example `next/image`).
- Clean up between tests to avoid cross-test leakage.
- Run tests with `npm run test:run` before finishing.

## Avoid

- Snapshot-only tests as the primary assertion strategy.
- Brittle selectors tied to DOM structure that is likely to change.
